default29.1.
default 
defaultGiving local government full control over council tax rates and discounts and removing requirements for referendums;
default&#xa0;
default29.2.
default 
defaultThe full localisation of business 
defaultrates which
default,
default if it took place
default,
default would mean local government could be self-funding in 2018-19 when the totality of business rates and council tax exceeds the current funding projections;
default&#xa0;
default29.3.
default 
defaultRemoving the centrally set Housing Revenue Account borrowing cap
default,
default allowing councils to build homes to full capacity. We estimate this could result in up to an additional 60,000 new homes over the next five years. Furthermore reforming the classification of council borrowing for housing would bring the UK into line with 
defaultEurope in the way it classifies this kind of borrowing and end the preoccupation with where the borrowing sits for accounting purposes
default,
default rather than the value attained for the investment
default. 
